goals.question: What is the overall trend in the number of people employed in different jobs over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart showing the trend in the number of people employed in different jobs over the years
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the overall trend in the job market and identify which jobs have seen an increase or decrease in employment over the years.

goals.question: What is the gender distribution in different jobs?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart showing the gender distribution in different jobs
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the gender distribution in different jobs and identify which jobs are male-dominated or female-dominated.

goals.question: What is the percentage of the total workforce represented by different jobs over the years?
goals.visualization: Area chart showing the percentage of the total workforce represented by different jobs over the years
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the relative importance of different jobs in the overall job market and identify which jobs have seen an increase or decrease in importance over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the number of people employed in different jobs?
goals.visualization: Histogram showing the distribution of the number of people employed in different jobs
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of the number of people employed in different jobs and identify which jobs have a high or low number of employees.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the percentage of the total workforce represented by different jobs?
goals.visualization: Histogram showing the distribution of the percentage of the total workforce represented by different jobs
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of the percentage of the total workforce represented by different jobs and identify which jobs have a high or low representation in the overall job market.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='year', y='count', hue='job', ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend in the number of people employed in different jobs over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    
    gender_dist = data.pivot_table(index='job', columns='sex', values='count', aggfunc='sum')
    gender_dist = gender_dist.div(gender_dist.sum(1), axis=0)
    gender_dist.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the gender distribution in different jobs?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.lineplot(data=data, x='year', y='perc', hue='job', ci=None)
    chart.set_title('What is the percentage of the total workforce represented by different jobs over the years?')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
